AC+AD<BC+BD
\frac{AC}{\sin b}=\frac{AB}{\sin c}=\frac{BC}{\sin(b+c)},
\frac{BD}{\sin a}=\frac{AB}{\sin d}=\frac{AD}{\sin(a+d)}.
AC=AB\frac{\sin b}{\sin c},\\ BC=AB\frac{\sin(b+c)}{\sin c},\\ BD=AB \frac{\sin a}{\sin d},\\ AD=AB\frac{\sin(a+d)}{\sin d}.
\frac{\sin b}{\sin c}+\frac{\sin(a+d)}{\sin d} > \frac{\sin(b+c)}{\sin c}+\frac{\sin a}{\sin d}.
